{"title":"Subscribe to Adventure Journal in Time for its Summer Issue","link":"https://theradavist.com/adventure-journal-summer-issue/","date":1715696137000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3639\" height=\"2426\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?fit=1200,2426&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?w=3639&amp;quality=75 3639w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW01.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>When it comes to inspirational print magazines, <a href=\"http://subscribetoaj.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Adventure Journal</a> checks all the boxes. We’re exceptionally pleased to share the cover of the summer issue of Adventure Journal with a photo by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/chrisburkard/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">@chrisburkard</a> that perfectly captures the spirit of this issue. Let’s take a look inside…<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW06.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW06.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW06.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW06.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW06.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW07.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW07.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW07.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW07.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/AJ33_JW07.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>John has some photos in this issue featuring singletrack riding, backpacking, and bike touring with some familiar faces, so don’t miss it!</em></p>\n<p>Adventure Journal is <strong>only</strong> available in print, and you can only get the issue by subscribing. Get yours at <a href=\"http://subscribetoaj.com/\" target=\"_blank\">subscribetoaj.com</a>. But act quickly—the magazine processes mailing labels next week.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/adventure-journal-summer-issue/\">Subscribe to Adventure Journal in Time for its Summer Issue</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"31f39e5043dfd9763a18cf60b5e85ed27d2b27b04ad7a7a21c2886ca804c091f","category":"Cycling"}